JetBrains Rider 2018.3 Help

Accessing Decompiled Files

All decompiled code that you can see in the editor editor is actually decompiled to temporary files. You can access these files if necessary.

To access decompiled files

  • To display the current file in its containing folder, right-click on the editor editor tab header and choose Show in Explorer/Finder.

  • To copy the path to the current file, right-click on the editor editor tab header and choose Copy Path (Ctrl+Shift+C) or Copy Relative Path (Ctrl+Shift+Alt+C).

  • You can also add the decompiled document to the favorites list for further reference — right-click on the editor tab header and choose Add to favorites.
